{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771082767,"nonce":"jDHYsqTI8tDNgnk2OfP5/NrLDe4=","title":"Admins and leaders can set other users' passwords directly","message":"Admins (via can :manage, :all) and leaders (via can :update, User in same department) can set passwords for other users through the user edit form. The user_params method permits :password and :password_confirmation without restricting who can set them.\n\nThis is a security anti-pattern: admins/leaders choose or know other users' passwords, and it bypasses Devise password-change notifications.\n\nSuggested fix: remove :password and :password_confirmation from user_params when editing other users. Admins should trigger a password reset email instead (Devise already supports this).","files":null}]}